# Generic JS/TS build output (apps/tools, not just packages/*/dist)
**/dist/
# Vendored manifest-runtime has no build step; its dist must be committed
# Route manifest artifacts must be committed for CI and dev-time validation
# manifest-adapters dist is consumed directly by apps/api (no publish step); must be committed
# sentry-integration dist must be committed — apps/api/app/webhooks/sentry/route.ts
# imports subpath exports (@repo/sentry-integration/queue, /webhook) that resolve
# to ./dist/*.d.ts via package.json exports. turbo typecheck doesn't depend on
# ^build, so CI sees no dist unless we commit it. Same pattern as manifest-adapters.
!packages/sentry-integration/dist/
!packages/sentry-integration/dist/**
# Same rationale for supplier-connectors — apps/api/app/api/webhooks/supplier-catalog/
# route.ts imports it; dist must be committed.
!packages/supplier-connectors/dist/
!packages/supplier-connectors/dist/**
**/build/
**/.output/
**/.vite/

